n </PERSON>'s defense attorney, said the explanation did not excuse the detectives' repeatedly fraudulent actions. `` It was not a lie. It was hundreds of lies,'' <PERSON> Stern </PERSON> said. `` And in an effort to reinstate the case, it was just more lies.'' Three detectives, <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Luna </PERSON>, 32, <PERSON> Hugo </PERSON> <PERSON> Amate </PERSON>, 31, and <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Schroeder </PERSON>, 33, have been suspended with pay while under investigation by <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> Attorney General <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Shannon </PERSON> for perjury.
