that I'd be thrilled to do the Oscars if they could just come up with an entrance,'' she said. `` And think of it, more than a billion and a half people just watched that. And at this very moment they're trying to make sense of it.'' As she made her entrance, <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Tomlin </PERSON> intentionally lost a shoe. She joked about it, recalling the late <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON>'s propensity for calling a really great show a `` really great shoe.'' A dancer from the chorus line crawled down the steps behind her, recovered the shoe and tossed it offstage.
