<TEXT>
 Hollywood's brightest stars were trying hard to keep their cool amid the competitive atmosphere of tonight's 61st Academy Awards ceremonies The extravaganza takes place against a feverish backdrop of ticket scalping, thievery, political demonstrations and last-minute preparations. Tickets for the ceremony were selling for more than $ 2,000 and Oscar guards were looking for someone who stole 40 passes for the show. Scores of fans who arrived early were eagerly awaiting the arrival of their favorite stars. Minutes after Oscar bleachers opened Tuesday afternoon, dozens of spectators streamed in. Thousands were expected by the show's opening.
